Subject: [PATCH AP-07] vmmon: add task->__state compat guard in hostif.c (kernel >= 5.14)

Linux 5.14 renamed task->state to task->__state and required direct reads
to use READ_ONCE(). VMware's hostif.c reads task state; without a version
guard, this causes a build error on kernel >= 5.14.

The fix adds a get_task_state() macro that selects the correct field name
and access method based on the kernel version. This guard is already present
in the community 6.16.x overlay and in VMware 25H2u1 sources — this patch
applies only when the guard is absent.

Applied by: _autopatch_hostif_task_state() in vmware_module_builder.py
Condition:  source does NOT already have the get_task_state compat guard

---
 vmmon-only/linux/hostif.c | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/vmmon-only/linux/hostif.c b/vmmon-only/linux/hostif.c
--- a/vmmon-only/linux/hostif.c
+++ b/vmmon-only/linux/hostif.c
@@ -<N>+<N>,7 @@
 #include "hostif.h"
+
+/* [autopatch] kernel 5.14+ renamed task->state to task->__state */
+#if LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= KERNEL_VERSION(5, 15, 0) || defined(get_current_state)
+#define get_task_state(task) READ_ONCE((task)->__state)
+#else
+#define get_task_state(task) ((task)->state)
+#endif
